article.headline: Rhode Island 75, Dayton 74
article.story: SOUTH KINGSTOWN, R.I. (AP) -- Jimmy Baron made a difficult lay-up with two seconds left to lift Rhode Island to a 75-74 win over Dayton Sunday. Baron had made three of nine shots prior to hitting the game-winner, but was able to get a wild lay-up attempt to bank high off the glass to provide the margin of victory. Will Daniels led Rhode Island with 19 points and scored 14 in the second half. Brian Roberts finished with 19 points for Dayton. Baron finished with eight points as Rhode Island (9-7, 2-0) overcame a 74-70 deficit in the final minute of play. There were 16 lead changes and eight ties in the game and neither team led by more than eight points. Dayton (11-4, 1-1) was up 41-40 at the half. Daniels made a 3-pointer with 6:53 remaining that gave Rhode Island a 64-62 edge and later pulled Rhode Island to 71-70 with a couple free throws with 2:43 left. Parfait Bitee chipped in with 11 points and five assists for Rhode Island but his defense may have been more crucial. He guarded Roberts for large stretches in the second half and denied him the ball on Dayton's final inbound play.
